## Continuous Checking

A `while` loop looks exactly like an `if` statement.

```dart
int health = 100;
while (health > 0) {
  print('Still alive!');
  health -= 10; // Take damage!
}
```
It checks `health > 0`. If true, it runs the block. Then it checks *again*. And *again*. Until it is false!

## Crashing the Matrix

If the condition in a `while` loop NEVER becomes false, your code will run completely out of control forever, freezing your app!

```dart
// This will crash your app!
int count = 0;
while (count < 5) {
  print('Hello!');
  // Wait... we forgot to add 1 to count!
}
```

